        "Here's how I implement A/B testing for clients:",
        "1. **Isolate Variables:** The key to effective A/B testing is to test only *one* variable at a time. This allows you to definitively attribute performance changes to that specific element.\n    - **Captions:** Test two different opening hooks, CTAs, or caption lengths.\n    - **Hashtags:** Test different sets of hashtags, or varying quantities.\n    - **Visuals:** Compare two different cover photos for a Reel, or two slightly different image styles for a post.\n    - **Posting Times:** Test posting the same type of content at different optimal times.\n    - **CTAs (Call to Action):** \"Shop Now\" vs. \"Learn More\" vs. \"Get Yours.\"\n    - **Reel Formats:** Compare a tutorial Reel vs. a trending sound Reel on the same topic.",
